### 3. RESOURCES (Read-Only Data Exposure)

MCP Resources expose LayerInfinite data as URI-addressable, subscribable resources. These are the "what can you read?" surface.

| URI Pattern | Description | Template Parameters | Returns |
|---|---|---|---|
| `layerinfinite://scores/{context_id}` | Ranked action scores for a context | `context_id`: UUID | ScoredAction[] + policy decision |
| `layerinfinite://scores/{context_id}?top_n=5` | Top-N scores | `top_n`: number (1-50) | Trimmed ScoredAction[] |
| `layerinfinite://patterns/{context_id}` | Successful action sequences | `context_id`: UUID | Episode patterns array |
| `layerinfinite://audit` | Paginated audit trail | Query params: cursor, session, action, from, to, limit | Outcome[] + pagination cursor |
| `layerinfinite://audit/{outcome_id}` | Single outcome detail | `outcome_id`: UUID | Full outcome with agent/action/context joins |
| `layerinfinite://agents/{agent_id}/trust` | Agent trust profile | `agent_id`: UUID | TrustScore, status, consecutive failures |
| `layerinfinite://actions` | All registered actions for customer | (none) | Action[] + total count |
| `layerinfinite://agents` | All agents for customer | (none) | Agent[] + trust summaries |
| `layerinfinite://contexts` | All contexts for customer | (none) | Context[] + outcome counts |
| `layerinfinite://health` | System health | (none) | Health check response |
| `layerinfinite://health/deep` | Deep diagnostics | (none) | Full diagnostic check |

**Resource implementation pattern** (each resource file):

```typescript
// src/resources/scores.ts
import { ResourceTemplate } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/mcp.js";

export const scoresResource = {
  uriTemplate: new ResourceTemplate("layerinfinite://scores/{contextId}", { list: undefined }),
  name: "Action Scores by Context",
  description: "Ranked action scores with policy decision for a given context",
  mimeType: "application/json",
  async handler(uri: URL, variables: { contextId: string }, context: any) {
    const apiClient = context.apiClient;
    const topN = uri.searchParams.get("top_n") || "10";
    const result = await apiClient.getScores({ 
      context_id: variables.contextId,
      top_n: parseInt(topN, 10)
    });
    return {
      contents: [{
        uri: uri.href,
        mimeType: "application/json",
        text: JSON.stringify(result, null, 2)
      }]
    };
  }
};
```

