### 4. TOOLS (Actions)

MCP Tools expose operations that LayerInfinite can perform. These are the "what can you do?" surface.

| Tool Name | Description | Input Schema | Maps to REST |
|---|---|---|---|
| `log-outcome` | Log an agent action outcome (append-only) | session_id, action_name, issue_type, success, outcome_score, response_time_ms, raw_context, verifier_signal, episode_id, idempotency_key, etc. | `POST /v1/log-outcome` |
| `get-scores` | Get ranked action scores for a context | issue_type OR context_id, top_n, force_refresh, episode_history | `GET /v1/get-scores` |
| `get-patterns` | Get historically successful action sequences | issue_type OR context_id, min_samples, top_n | `GET /v1/get-patterns` |
| `submit-feedback` | Submit delayed outcome feedback | outcome_id, final_score, business_outcome, feedback_notes | `POST /v1/outcome-feedback` |
| `simulate-sequence` | Simulate proposed action sequences | agent_id, context (object), proposed_sequence, episode_history, simulate_alternatives | `POST /v1/simulate` |
| `admin_register-action` | Register a new action (admin) | action_name, action_category, action_description, required_params | `POST /v1/admin/register-action` |
| `admin_list-actions` | List all registered actions | (none) | `GET /v1/admin/actions` |
| `admin_get-action` | Get single action by ID | action_id | `GET /v1/admin/actions/:id` |
| `admin_toggle-action` | Enable/disable an action | action_id, is_active | `PUT /v1/admin/actions/:id` |
| `admin_reinstate-agent` | Reinstate a suspended agent | agent_id, reinstated_by | `POST /v1/admin/reinstate-agent` |

**Tool implementation pattern**:

```typescript
// src/tools/log-outcome.ts
import { z } from "zod";

const LogOutcomeSchema = z.object({
  session_id: z.string().uuid().optional(),
  action_name: z.string().min(1).max(255),
  issue_type: z.string().min(1).max(255),
  success: z.boolean(),
  outcome_score: z.number().min(0).max(1).optional(),
  response_time_ms: z.number().int().positive().optional(),
  raw_context: z.record(z.string(), z.unknown()).optional(),
  idempotency_key: z.string().max(255).optional(),
  episode_id: z.string().uuid().optional(),
  verifier_signal: z.object({
    source: z.enum(["http_status_code", "database_row_count", "human_review", "downstream_webhook", "none"]),
    value: z.union([z.number(), z.boolean(), z.string()]).optional(),
  }).optional(),
});

export const logOutcomeTool = {
  name: "log-outcome",
  description: "Log an agent action outcome to LayerInfinite. Updates trust scores, triggers policy decisions, and feeds the scoring engine.",
  inputSchema: LogOutcomeSchema,
  async handler(args: z.infer<typeof LogOutcomeSchema>, context: any) {
    return await context.apiClient.postLogOutcome(args);
  }
};
```

