### 5. PROMPTS (Templates)

MCP Prompts are reusable prompt templates that orchestrate multiple tool calls.

| Prompt Name | Description | Input | Behind the Scenes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `analyze-agent-performance` | Comprehensive agent analysis | `agent_id`, `issue_type` | Calls `get-scores` + reads `agents/{id}/trust` resource + reads `audit` filtered by agent_id |
| `respond-to-context` | Get recommendation for a situation | `issue_type`, `raw_context`, `episode_history` | Calls `get-patterns` + `get-scores` + policy decision |
| `agent-health-check` | Check agent trust and performance | `agent_id` | Reads trust resource + recent outcomes from audit |
| `explore-counterfactuals` | Simulate alternative action sequences | `agent_id`, `context`, `proposed_sequence` | Calls `simulate-sequence` and returns comparison table |

**Prompt implementation pattern**:

```typescript
