### 7. ERROR HANDLING

LayerInfinite REST errors map to MCP error codes as follows:

| LayerInfinite HTTP Status | LayerInfinite Error Code | MCP Error Code | MCP Error Message |
|---|---|---|---|
| 401 | `MISSING_API_KEY` | `-32001` (Unauthorized) | "Missing or invalid API key. Set LAYERINFINITE_API_KEY in your environment." |
| 401 | `INVALID_API_KEY` | `-32001` | "Invalid API key. Check your LAYERINFINITE_API_KEY environment variable." |
| 400 | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | `-32602` (InvalidParams) | "Invalid request parameters: {details}" |
| 404 | `NOT_FOUND` | `-32602` | "Resource not found: {details}" |
| 409 | `CONFLICT` | `-32603` | "Conflict: {message}" |
| 413 | `PAYLOAD_TOO_LARGE` | `-32602` | "Payload exceeds 64KB limit" |
| 429 | (rate limit) | `-32005` (RateLimited) | "Rate limit exceeded. Retry after {retryAfter}s" |
| 500 | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | `-32603` (InternalError) | "LayerInfinite internal error: {message}" |
| 503 | `AUTH_ERROR` | `-32001` | "Authentication service unavailable" |

**Error mapping implementation** (`src/lib/error-map.ts`):

```typescript
import { McpError, ErrorCode } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/types.js";

export function mapRestError(status: number, body: any): McpError {
  switch (status) {
    case 401:
      return new McpError(-32001, body?.error ?? "Authentication failed");
    case 429:
      return new McpError(-32005, "Rate limit exceeded");
    case 404:
      return new McpError(ErrorCode.InvalidParams, body?.error ?? "Not found");
    case 400:
      const detail = body?.details ? `: ${body.details}` : "";
      return new McpError(ErrorCode.InvalidParams, `${body?.error ?? "Bad request"}${detail}`);
    case 409:
      return new McpError(-32603, body?.error ?? "Conflict");
    case 413:
      return new McpError(ErrorCode.InvalidParams, "Payload too large");
    default:
      return new McpError(ErrorCode.InternalError, body?.error ?? "Unknown error");
  }
}
```

