### 14. DIFFERENCES FROM THE EXISTING SDK

The existing TypeScript SDK (`layer5/sdks/typescript/`) is a raw HTTP client. The MCP server is fundamentally different:

| Aspect | Existing SDK | MCP Server |
|---|---|---|
| Consumer | TypeScript applications | Any MCP-compatible platform (Claude Desktop, Cursor, VS Code, Windsurf, OpenClaw) |
| Integration | `npm install @layerinfinite/sdk` + manual HTTP calls | Zero-code -- add JSON config to MCP host's config |
| Auth | `new LayerInfiniteClient({ apiKey })` | `LAYERINFINITE_API_KEY` env var passed from MCP host |
| Resources | N/A -- no URI-addressable data | 10+ URI templates for data exploration |
| Tools | SDK methods map to REST 1:1 | Same + resource-aware tool composition |
| Prompts | N/A | 4 built-in templates that compose tools + resources |

The MCP server does **not** replace the SDK. It wraps the REST API such that any LLM platform that speaks MCP can use LayerInfinite without writing a single line of code.

